      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Todd in Greensboro
      4.0 out of 5 stars Meh - it's OK but an oddity
      Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2023
      Color: BeigeVerified Purchase
      UPDATED
      Increasing from 3 start to 4 stars because a few days after I left my 3 star review (neutral), the vendor sent me a message offering a full refund. The refund offer did not have any conditions attached to it. That demonstrates to me that the vendor is responsive to issues.
      ******
      It is OK, but has some drawbacks. I did not buy this for the cute color scheme, but rather because it was a value-priced mechanical keyboard. Those reviewers giving this a 5-star review probably don't know what a mechanical keyboard is supposed to feel like. The mechanical key switches are pretty loose/sloppy feeling. They have very long travel, with a loud tactile click about half-way through the key press. But they do not feel very precision and have terrible wobble and slop within the keypress that I found distracting. When I ordered it, I did not think that the round keycaps would be a problem, but as a touch typist, I found them more difficult to use than traditional square keycaps that have more surface area. It does have some interesting backlighting and keycap lighting effects, with many settings. It is a shame that the key shafts are wobbly, which makes this keyboard completely unusable for me for serious typing. Still, it's a mechanical keyboard at a value price, so I am giving three stars.
